{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotmanager"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Snapshots","generated":true,"anchor":"Snapshots","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotError"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"SnapshotManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the VM’s disk image ("},{"code":"disk.img","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") and auxiliary storage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"auxiliary.bin"},{"text":"), stored in a named subdirectory under the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"SavedStates\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" directory.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work","type":"heading","text":"How Snapshots Work"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The VM "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must be stopped"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" before saving or restoring."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with the snapshot copies."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"APFS-Copy-on-Write","text":"APFS Copy-on-Write","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On APFS volumes, both save and restore use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileManager.copyItem"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which the system maps to "},{"code":"clonefile(2)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This produces a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"copy-on-write clone instead of a byte-for-byte copy, making","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"snapshot creation and restoration near-instantaneous regardless"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of disk image size. Only blocks that diverge after the clone"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consume additional storage.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Snapshot Directory Layout"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"]},{"anchor":"Example","text":"Example","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"codeListing